article.headline: King scores 24, Richmond knocks off George Washington 90-74
article.description: — Jordan King scored 24 points as Richmond beat George Washington 90-74 on Saturday.
article.linkText: King scores 24, Richmond knocks off George Washington 90-74
article.story: WASHINGTON -- — Jordan King scored 24 points as Richmond beat George Washington 90-74 on Saturday. King was 7 of 13 shooting, including 2 for 4 from 3-point range, and went 8 for 8 from the line for the Spiders (18-7, 10-2 Atlantic 10 Conference). Neal Quinn scored 19 points and added five rebounds, seven assists, and three blocks. Dji Bailey went 8 of 12 from the field to finish with 16 points. James Bishop IV finished with 23 points and four assists for the Revolutionaries (14-11, 3-9). Maximus Edwards added 19 points for George Washington. In addition, Jacoi Hutchinson finished with 15 points. The Revolutionaries extended their losing streak to eight straight. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
